UTILIZATION REVIEW REQUIREMENTS (§ 29-4109)
    In accordance with 42 C.F.R. § 456.401, each ICF/IID shall develop, implement,nd maintain a written Utilization Review Plan (URP) for each Medicaideneficiary receiving services furnished by the ICF/IID. The URP shall provideor a review of each beneficiary’s
      need for the services that the ICFurnished him or her.
    Utilization review for ICFs/IID enrolled in D.C. Medicaid may beonducted by any of the following:
    The ICF/IID;
    DHCF or its designee; or
    Any other approved method.
    The URP shall, at minimum, include the following:
    A description of how utilization review shall be performed;
    The frequency of utilization review;
    Assurances and documentation establishing that the personnel who shall performtilization review meet the requirements of 42 C.F.R. § 456.406;
    Administrative staff responsibilities related to utilization review;
    The types of records maintained by the utilization review team;
    The types and frequency of any reports developed by the utilization review team,nd related plan for dissemination; and
    The procedures that shall be used when corrective action is necessary.
    In accordance with 42 C.F.R. §§ 456.431 &#8211; 456.438, each URPhall establish a process whereby each individual residing in the ICF/IIDeceives continued stay reviews, at minimum, every six (6) months.
    The URP shall establish written methods and criteria used to conductontinued stay reviews. The URP shall also set forth enhanced criteria used tossess a case if the individual’s circumstances reflect any of the followingssociations:
    High costs;
    Frequent and excessive services; or
    Attended by a physician or other practitioner whose practices reflectuestionable billing patterns or misrepresentation of facts needed in order toecure claims reimbursement, including but not limited to ordering and/orroviding services that are not
      medically necessary or that fail to meetrofessionally recognized standards of care.
